<HL>
   Who's News:
   Riser Foods Realigns
   Management Positions
</HL>
<DATE>
06/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6
</SO>
<CO>
   WNEWS RSR
</CO>
<LP>
   BEDFORD HEIGHTS, Ohio -- Riser Foods Inc. said Anthony
Rego, who had been a co-chairman of the food store chain, was
named chairman and chief executive officer.
   Mr. Rego, 48 years old, who will be responsible for
corporate administration, direction and planning, said the
move is aimed at clarifying the company's chain of command
and improving operating efficiency.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Michael Borstein, 51, who had shared the chairman's
position with Mr. Rego, was named vice chairman. He will be
responsible for the company's Seaway Foods wholesale
operations.
   As part of the changes, the company said Anthony Petrillo
stepped down as executive vice president, but now is a
consultant to Riser management.
   Charles Rini continues as president and chief operating
officer at Riser, the company said.
</TEXT>
