<HL>
   Swiss Jobless Rate Unchanged
</HL>
<DATE>
06/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   BERN, Switzerland -- Switzerland's jobless rate of 0.5% in
May was unchanged from April, but was down from 0.6% a year
earlier, the government said.
   Despite the flat unemployment rate in May, the number of
unemployed people fell to 15,979 from 16,634 in April. In May
1989, the number of jobless stood at 17,225. The number of
unfilled jobs declined to 18,376 in May from 18,701 in April,
but rose from 18,031 a year earlier.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The May jobless rate among men was 0.4%, and among women,
0.7%.
</TEXT>
