<HL>
   Treasury Plans Sale
   Of Notes Next Week
</HL>
<DATE>
06/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C19
</SO>
<IN>
CDS, INTEREST RATES, COMMERCIAL PAPER (FIN)
BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)
</IN>
<GV>
TREASURY DEPARTMENT (TRE)
</GV>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- The Treasury plans to raise $2.18 billion in
new cash with the sale Tuesday of about $11.25 billion in
two-year notes and the sale Wednesday of about $8.25 billion
in four-year notes to redeem $17.32 billion in maturing
securities.
   The offerings mature on June 30, 1992, and June 30, 1994,
respectively.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Tenders for the two-year notes, available in minimum
$5,000 denominations, must be received by 1 p.m. EDT Tuesday
at the Treasury or at Federal Reserve banks or branches.
   Tenders for the four-year notes, available in minimum
$1,000 denominations, must be received by 1 p.m. EDT
Wednesday at the Treasury or at Federal Reserve banks or
branches.
</TEXT>
