<HL>
   International Brief -- British Coal Corp.:
   Pension Funds Increase Bid
   For Globe Investment Trust
</HL>
<DATE>
06/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A10
</SO>
<CO>
   U.BCC U.GLO LABOR
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   British Coal Corp.'s pension funds increased their hostile
takeover offer for Globe Investment Trust PLC's ordinary
shares to 205 pence ($3.53) from 191 pence.
   The new offer, which the pension funds declared final
unless a rival bidder appears, values Globe at #1.11 billion
($1.91 billion).
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The coal pension funds launched their bid in April and had
succeeded in gaining acceptances for only 1.42% of Globe
shares. Prior to launching the bid, the pension funds owned
slightly less than 34% of Globe.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
